  "section_name": "Risk Analysis",
  "text": "Revenue growth volatility presents a moderate risk factor. Year-over-year revenue growth has fluctuated significantly across recent quarters, ranging from -0.93% in Q1 2025 to 7.22% in Q2 2025, before moderating to 0.91% in Q3 2025. This inconsistency suggests the company's top-line performance may be sensitive to macroeconomic conditions or consumer spending patterns. Net income growth has shown similar variability, with Q3 2025 growing only 0.59% year-over-year compared to 11.65% in Q2 2025. Such volatility could indicate exposure to economic cycles affecting cardholder spending and merchant transaction volumes.",
